        	<div id="content">
                <div id="content_left">

					<h1>Globus Online: Use The Grid</h1>
					<div align="center" style="margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px"><a href="http://www.globusonline.org"><img src="img/home/go_logo_200.png" /></a></div>
					<p>Globus Online makes grid capabilities immediately available via a 
					cloud-hosted online service. Use Globus Online to move big data securely 
					and reliably among local and distributed computing resources &mdash; without 
					complex software installation, configuration, and administrative hassles. 
					<a class="more" href="http://www.globusonline.org">Start using the grid...</a></p>     
                    
                    <h2>dev.globus Developer Community</h2>
                    <p>The Globus Alliance is an active member in the community of Grid 
                    Software developers.
                    <a class="more" href="http://dev.globus.org">Learn more...</a></p> 
           
			        <h2>Initiative for Globus in Europe</h2>
                    <div align="center" style="margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px;"><a href="http://www.ige-project.eu/"><img src="img/home/logo_IGE.png" width="200" /></a></div>
<p>The Initiative for Globus in Europe (IGE) is a project providing European 
                    researchers with the tools to share computing power, databases, instruments, 
                    and other on-line tools. The University of Chicago and Argonne National 
Laboratory are full project partners in IGE.
                    <a class="more" href="http://www.ige-project.eu/">Visit IGE web site...</a>
                    </p>
                    
                </div>
                <div id="content_right">
                    
					<h1>Globus Toolkit: Build The Grid</h1>
					<div align="center" style="margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px"><a href="/toolkit/"><img src="img/home/toolkit_logo_200_noname.png" /></a></div>
					<p>The Globus Toolkit is a fundamental enabling technology for building 
					grids that allow distributed computing power, storage resources, 
					scientific instruments, and other tools to be shared securely across 
					corporate, institutional, and geographic boundaries.
                    <a class="more" href="/toolkit/">Start building your grid...</a></p>
                    
                    <h2>Globus Alliance</h2>
                    <p>The Globus Alliance is a community of organizations and individuals 
                    developing fundamental technologies behind the "Grid".
                    <a class="more" href="/alliance/">Learn more...</a>
                    </p>
                    
					<h2>European Globus Community Forum</h2>
	                <div align="center" style="margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px;"><a href="http://www.egcf.eu/"><img src="img/home/logo_EGCF.png" width="200" /></a></div>
                    <p>The European Globus Community Forum (EGCF) is the organizational body 
                    of the Globus community in Europe.
                    <a class="more" href="http://www.egcf.eu/">Learn more...</a></p> 
                    
                </div>
